  "help_desc":        "FinanceTracker — a personal finance tracking app.\nTrack income, expenses, categories and savings goals.",

  "faq_q1": "How to add a new transaction?",
  "faq_a1": "Go to the Transactions screen. Click '+ Add' next to 'Transaction history'. Enter the amount, type, category, vendor and note.",
  "faq_q2": "How to quickly top up the balance?",
  "faq_a2": "On the Transactions screen, click 'Deposit +' in the top right corner. Enter the amount and click 'Confirm' — balance updates instantly.",
  "faq_q3": "How to create a savings goal?",
  "faq_a3": "Open Goals and click '+ Create goal'. Enter the name, icon, target amount and duration. Add funds via '+ Add funds' on the goal card.",
  "faq_q4": "How to add a category with a limit?",
  "faq_a4": "In Categories, click '+ Add category'. Enter a name, emoji icon and monthly spending limit.",
  "faq_q5": "What does the Analytics screen show?",
  "faq_a5": "Analytics compares the current month with the previous one: expense change percentage, top-spending category and a comparison table.",
  "faq_q6": "How to export data?",
  "faq_a6": "In Settings, select data types, choose format (.JSON/.CSV/.EXCEL) and a folder, then click 'Export data'.",
  "faq_q7": "What is the difference between .JSON, .CSV and .EXCEL?",
  "faq_a7": "JSON — full backup. CSV — table for Excel/Google Sheets. EXCEL — .xlsx with colored headers for analysis.",
  "faq_q8": "What currency is used?",
  "faq_a8": "Kyrgyz som (с). Amounts use a dot as the thousands separator: 48.200 с."
